description: Gets a list of attachments associated with an Amazon Q Business web experience or a list of attachements associated with a specific Amazon Q Business conversation.

parameters.name: applicationId
parameters.description: The unique identifier for the Amazon Q Business application.

nested_items.name: attachments
nested_items.description: An array of information on one or more attachments.

nested_items.name: attachmentId
nested_items.description: The identifier of the Amazon Q Business attachment.

nested_items.name: conversationId
nested_items.description: The identifier of the Amazon Q Business conversation the attachment is associated with.

nested_items.name: name
nested_items.description: Filename of the Amazon Q Business attachment.

nested_items.name: conversation
nested_items.description: A reference to an attachment in an existing conversation.

nested_items.name: conversationId
nested_items.description: The unique identifier of the Amazon Q Business conversation.

nested_items.name: attachmentId
nested_items.description: The unique identifier of the Amazon Q Business attachment.

nested_items.name: fileType
nested_items.description: Filetype of the Amazon Q Business attachment.

nested_items.name: fileSize
nested_items.description: Size in bytes of the Amazon Q Business attachment.

nested_items.name: md5chksum
nested_items.description: MD5 checksum of the Amazon Q Business attachment contents.

nested_items.name: createdAt
nested_items.description: The Unix timestamp when the Amazon Q Business attachment was created.

nested_items.name: status
nested_items.description: AttachmentStatus of the Amazon Q Business attachment.

nested_items.name: errorMessage
nested_items.description: The message explaining the Amazon Q Business request error.

nested_items.name: errorCode
nested_items.description: The code associated with the Amazon Q Business request error.

nested_items.name: nextToken
nested_items.description: If the response is truncated, Amazon Q Business returns this token, which you can use in a later request to list the next set of attachments.
